		"notes": [
			{
				"category": "summary",
				"text": "An update for xmlrpc is now available for Red Hat Virtualization 4 for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.\n\nRed Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Moderate. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.",
				"title": "Topic"
			},
			{
				"category": "general",
				"text": "XML-RPC is a way to make remote procedure calls over the Internet. It converts procedure calls into XML documents, sends them to a remote server using the HTTP protocol, and gets back the response as XML.\n\nThe following packages have been upgraded to a later upstream version: xmlrpc (3.1.3). (BZ#1594618)\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* xmlrpc: Deserialization of untrusted Java object through <ex:serializable> tag (CVE-2016-5003)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
				"title": "Details"
			},
			{
				"category": "legal_disclaimer",
